section1.title: your application
section1.custom_description: We’re so excited that you want to come to TreeHacks 2020! Let’s start with the basics.

resume.title: Resume
resume.description: Upload your resume (optional) - Must be a PDF file, 10 MB max

accept_terms.title: I have read and agree to the TreeHacks Code of Conduct.

accept_share.title: I authorize you to share my application/registration information for purposes in-line with the TreeHacks Privacy Policy.

section2.title: short answer questions
section2.custom_description: We strive to admit a diverse group of hackers of all experience levels who will make the most of their time at TreeHacks. Help us get to know you and how awesome you are!

q1.title: Why do you want to come to TreeHacks 2020?

q2.title: Tell us about a project that you've worked on in the past, technical or nontechnical. Why did you choose to work on it?

q3.title: Tell us about something that is meaningful to you, and why?

q4.title: Tell us a fun fact about you :)

q5.title: Optionally, add any links (separated by commas) that you'd like us to check out! GitHub, LinkedIn, Devpost, Dribbble, etc.

volunteer.title: Volunteer
volunteer.description: Are you interested in volunteering at the event?

section3.title: other questions
section3.custom_description: You’re almost there — last few questions! These are optional, but all of our applicants are super interesting, and we want to learn as much as we can about what makes you you!

q_team_matching_1.title: I would describe myself as a...

q_team_matching_2.title: Is there anything else that we should know about you? (optional!)
